JA  - Advanced Information Networking and Applications (AINA), 2010 24th IEEE International Conference on
DO  - 10.1109/AINA.2010.26
AB  - Trustable log data is essential in digital forensic investigations in order to allow reliable reconstruction of events. Existing solutions do not provide adequate protection, exposing the log-producing application to software-based attacks. In this paper we provide a solution based on Trusted Computing using a Trusted Platform Module (TPM) and AMD's Secure Virtual Machine technology (SVM). While current solutions only protect against manipulation of existing logs, we go one step further by establishing hardware-based trust in the log producing application. Our solution ensures confidentiality, integrity and non-repudiation during creation, storage and transmission of log data.
