AU  - Hai-Tao Lin
Y1  - 9-11 Sept. 2013
PY  - 2013
KW  - public key cryptography
KW  - attribute-based cryptographic schemes
KW  - attribute-based signature
KW  - cipher text-policy attribute-based encryption
KW  - forgery attack
KW  - security analysis
KW  - threshold attribute-based signcryption scheme
KW  - Encryption
KW  - Games
KW  - Identity-based encryption
KW  - Polynomials
KW  - attribute-based encryption
KW  - attribute-based signature
KW  - bilinear pairings
KW  - threshold attribute-based signcryption
VL  - 
JA  - Intelligent Networking and Collaborative Systems (INCoS), 2013 5th International Conference on
DO  - 10.1109/INCoS.2013.23
AB  - In SCN2010, Gagne, Narayan, and Safavi-Naini proposed attribute-based signcryption with threshold structure. As in cipher text-policy attribute-based encryption, a sender can specify the access structure of recipients, and as in attribute-based signature, each recipient can verify the sender's attributes. In contrast to the access structure of recipients, the access structure of the sender needs to be fixed in the setup phase. In this paper, we show that Gagne et al.'s threshold attribute-based signcryption is not secure and give a concrete forgery attack. The attack can make use some keys to construct any other legal keys and at last totally break the scheme. We also show that the attack is effective on other attribute-based cryptographic schemes with the same key structure.
ER  - 

